## Anti-Pattern Detection Rules

### RULE 1: Unsafe Deserialization — CWE-502

**Severity: Critical | Typically leads to RCE**

**BAD — Deserializing untrusted data:**
```
// Java
ObjectInputStream ois = new ObjectInputStream(untrustedStream);
Object obj = ois.readObject();                         // Arbitrary class instantiation

// Python
data = pickle.loads(untrusted_bytes)                   // Code execution
data = yaml.load(untrusted_string)                     // Without SafeLoader = RCE
data = marshal.load(untrusted_file)                    // Code execution

// PHP
obj = unserialize(user_input)                          // POP chain → RCE

// Ruby
obj = Marshal.load(untrusted_data)                     // Code execution
data = YAML.load(untrusted_string)                     // Object instantiation

// .NET
BinaryFormatter.Deserialize(untrustedStream)           // RCE
NetDataContractSerializer.ReadObject(untrustedStream)  // RCE

// Node.js
require("node-serialize").unserialize(user_input)      // RCE via IIFE
```

**GOOD — Safe alternatives:**
```
// Java: Allowlist-based filtering
ObjectInputStream ois = new ValidatingObjectInputStream(stream);
ois.accept(AllowedClass1.class, AllowedClass2.class);
// Or: Use JSON with Jackson (default typing DISABLED)
objectMapper.configure(ENABLE_DEFAULT_TYPING, false);

// Python
data = yaml.safe_load(untrusted_string)       // SafeLoader only
data = json.loads(untrusted_string)            // JSON instead of pickle

// PHP
data = json_decode(user_input)                 // JSON instead of unserialize

// .NET
JsonSerializer.Deserialize(stream)             // System.Text.Json
// Or: Newtonsoft with TypeNameHandling.None (NEVER Auto or All)
```

**Also check for:**
- Jackson with `enableDefaultTyping()` or `@JsonTypeInfo` with `Id.CLASS` — allows polymorphic RCE
- Newtonsoft Json.NET with `TypeNameHandling.Auto` or `TypeNameHandling.All`
- Java XMLDecoder, XStream without security framework
- SnakeYAML without `SafeConstructor`
- Gadget chain availability: check project dependencies for known gadget classes (commons-collections, spring-beans, etc.)

