### RULE 2: XML External Entity (XXE) — CWE-611

**BAD — XML parsing with external entities enabled:**
```
// Default parsers often enable external entities
parser = XMLParser()
doc = parser.parse(untrusted_xml)

// Java
DocumentBuilderFactory factory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
Document doc = factory.newDocumentBuilder().parse(input);  // XXE enabled by default

// Python
tree = etree.parse(untrusted_xml)                          // lxml default allows XXE

// .NET
XmlDocument doc = new XmlDocument();
doc.LoadXml(untrusted_xml);                                // XXE in older .NET
```

**GOOD — External entities disabled:**
```
// Java
DocumentBuilderFactory factory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
factory.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl", true);
factory.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities", false);
factory.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities", false);
factory.setXIncludeAware(false);
factory.setExpandEntityReferences(false);

// Python
parser = etree.XMLParser(resolve_entities=False, no_network=True)
// Or: Use defusedxml
import defusedxml.ElementTree as ET

// .NET
XmlReaderSettings settings = new XmlReaderSettings();
settings.DtdProcessing = DtdProcessing.Prohibit;
```

**Also check for:**
- Billion laughs attack (entity expansion DoS) — even without external entities
- SSRF via XXE (using `file:///` or `http://internal-host/` in entity definitions)
- SVG file uploads containing XML with entities (SVG is XML)
- XSLT processing with user-controlled stylesheets
- SOAP endpoints consuming XML without entity restrictions

