### RULE 3: Type Confusion / Polymorphic Deserialization — CWE-843

**BAD — Accepting arbitrary types:**
```
// JSON with type discriminator from user input
@JsonTypeInfo(use = Id.CLASS)           // Attacker controls class instantiation
class Message { Object payload; }       // Generic Object = any type

// TypeScript/JavaScript
JSON.parse(input, reviver)              // Custom reviver reconstructing objects
```

**GOOD — Strict type allowlisting:**
```
// Jackson: allowlist specific subtypes
@JsonTypeInfo(use = Id.NAME)
@JsonSubTypes({
    @Type(value = TextMessage.class, name = "text"),
    @Type(value = ImageMessage.class, name = "image")
})
abstract class Message {}

// Validate type field against allowlist before processing
VALID_TYPES = {"text", "image", "file"}
IF payload.type NOT IN VALID_TYPES: REJECT
```

**Also check for:**
- Protobuf/gRPC: unknown field handling, field number reuse between versions
- GraphQL: deeply nested queries causing DoS (query depth/complexity limits needed)
- MessagePack, CBOR, Avro with type tags from untrusted input

