### RULE 4: Prototype Pollution — CWE-1321

**BAD — Merging user input into objects:**
```
// JavaScript
Object.assign(target, JSON.parse(userInput))
_.merge(config, userInput)                    // lodash deep merge
target = {...defaults, ...userInput}          // Spread with __proto__

// User sends: {"__proto__": {"isAdmin": true}}
// Now ALL objects have isAdmin = true
```

**GOOD — Sanitize before merge:**
```
// Strip dangerous keys before merging
FUNCTION safe_merge(target, source):
    FOR key IN source:
        IF key IN ["__proto__", "constructor", "prototype"]: CONTINUE
        target[key] = source[key]

// Or: Use Object.create(null) for config objects (no prototype chain)
config = Object.create(null)

// Or: Use Map instead of plain objects for dynamic keys
```

